ning or uncertainty quantification, but have not integrated these components effectively. Additionally, interpretability remains a significant challenge in deep learning models. The integration of Bayesian principles and symbolic regression in a unified framework is a novel approach that has not been fully explored.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\n- **Refined:** The proposed approach involves developing a hierarchical model that integrates Bayesian principles for uncertainty quantification and symbolic regression for interpretability. The model will be evaluated on complex image datasets, such as COCO and ImageNet, and metrics such as compositional generalization, interpretability (using symbolic regression), and uncertainty estimates (using Bayesian principles) will be used to assess performance.\n\nBy refining these questions, the research proposal becomes more focused and actionable. The next step would be to draft the research paper based on this refined proposal.", 'agent3': "Given the detailed analysis and the proposed research idea, the next logical step is to refine the research proposal and ensure that all aspects are clearly articulated and feasible. Here are the next steps:\n\n1. **Refine the Research Proposal:**\n   - Ensure that the research questions are specific and well-defined.\n   - Clarify the methodology and the steps involved in the research.\n   - Make sure the expected outcomes are realistic and measurable.\n\n2. **Develop a Detailed Methodology:**\n   - Specify the datasets to be used for training and evaluation.\n   - Outline the specific techniques and algorithms to be implemented.\n   - Define the metrics for evaluating the performance of the model.\n\n3. **Prepare a Draft of the Research Paper:**\n   - Write an initial draft of the research paper, including the introduction, methodology, results, and discussion sections.\n   - Ensure that the paper is well-structured and logically coherent.\n