or efficient algorithms to handle large datasets and the development of methods to ensure that learned representations are both interpretable and useful for downstream tasks.",\n\n  "[Question 4] - Why hasn\'t it been solved before?": "Previous research has focused on developing models that can learn hierarchical representations from non-linguistic data, but there is a gap in terms of scalability and interpretability. Existing models often struggle with handling complex scenes and providing reliable uncertainty estimates. The challenge lies in balancing the need for expressive models with the practical constraints of computational efficiency and interpretability. Our approach aims to address these gaps by incorporating attention mechanisms, modular architectures, and disentangled representation learning.",\n\n  "[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?": "Our proposed methodology includes the development of a hierarchical Semantic Vector-Quantized Variational Autoencoder (SVQ-VAE) with attention mechanisms and a modular architecture to enhance scalability. We will also use disentangled representation learning and symbolic regression techniques to improve interpretability. The model will be evaluated on complex image datasets, such as COCO and ShapeNet, using metrics such as generation quality, interpretability, and generalization. We expect the model to outperform existing approaches in terms of handling complex scenes and providing reliable uncertainty estimates, leading to more robust and versatile representations."\n}\n```', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': [], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent_kpis': {}}, {'iteration': 3, 'task_assignments': {'agent1': "Given the structured approach outlined, the next logical step is to **Refine the Research Proposal**. This step is crucial as it ensures that the objectives, methodologies, datasets, and evaluation metrics are clearly defined and achievable. Here’s a detailed breakdown of w